dc:description: Rim outsplayed and folded up to yield vertical sides. Narrow mouth opening. Short asymmetrical neck broadens into pear shaped body. Once had a cylindrical foot, now broken off. Shallow ridges ring bottom half of vessel. Yellowish clay, unglazed. Chips around rim. Four shallow chipped abrasions at regular intervals around widest part of vase. Perhaps was held in place by 4 prongs? Maybe knob handles located there.
